                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1121 Wong Bock Yue/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-01T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 1, 1930—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 1—4:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>651. Department’s 239, July 17, 7 p.m. Legation is today informed through the
                    Diplomatic Bureau that the authorities Garrison Headquarters state food, drink,
                    sleeping and living quarters of Garrison Headquarters house of detention are
                    sanitary and that no discrimination exists in case of Wong Bock Yue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
